{
  "texts": [
    "The mention of a disease might not necessarily come with descriptors of its prevalence unless it's rare.",
    "For example, in the sentence, \"Ablepharon-Macrostomia Syndrome (AMS) is an extremely rare inherited disorder,\" \"inherited disorder\" is a disease.",
    "SymptomSymptoms are subjective and detected by the patient.",
    "For example, in the sentence, \"In the acute form, drowsiness, coma, and seizures may occur,\" \"drowsiness\" is a symptom, but \"coma\" and \"seizures\" are not.",
    "SignSigns can be measured or observed and don't rely on the patient's subjective reporting."
  ]
}